==English==
===Verb===
'''[[speak]] [[up]]'''
#{{idiom}} To talk more [[loudly]] or [[plainly]].
#:''Could you '''speak up'''?  I can't hear you.''
#{{idiom}} To make oneself or one's [[opinions]] known; to [[advocate]] or [[assert]] oneself.
#:''I feel that somebody has to '''speak up''' for those oppressed by the system.''
#:'''''Speak up''' if I'm bothering you.''

